The paper proposes a method for improving instance segmentation performance using a network block to learn the quality of predicted instance masks. This problem is specific to computer vision tasks, particularly instance segmentation, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed method involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the calibration of misalignment between mask quality and mask score, which is a common problem in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, and cs.MM, in that order.
